Fixing a call to a nonexistent method in UITableViewController.
A method of UITableView called "initWithStyle" was being called, but that
method doesn't actually exist. Now, it calls "initWithFrame:style:" using the
frame of the view of the parent view controller. I'm not sure if that's the
correct way of handling this, but it seems to work properly.
